#X text 50 33 When a control input signal increases above a threshold level \, the input signal gets attenuated. The attenuation ratio relates to how much the control signal has exceeded the threshold. For instance \, if the signal has increased 10 dB over the threshold and the ratio is 1 \, then the inoput signal gets attenuated by 10 dB. A ratio of 0.5 decreases 5 dB \, 2 corresponds to 20 dB and so on., f 58;
